N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 4 ยง 214.1 - Misconduct by any person

State Regulations

Misconduct by any person at any stage of a case before the
board, an administrative law judge or other person designated by the board to
conduct proceedings, may be grounds for summary exclusion by the board, administrative law judge, or other designee before whom the misconduct
occurred. Notes
